<script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@graph":[{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://stackarchitect.xyz/faq/what-is-make-com#webpage","url":"https://stackarchitect.xyz/faq/what-is-make-com","name":"What Is Make.com? — Explained for Shopify Store Owners | Stack Architect","description":"Make.com (formerly Integromat) is a no-code automation platform. For Shopify stores it powers server-side tracking, inventory management, TikTok CAPI, and P&L reporting — all on the free tier.","datePublished":"2026-04-21","dateModified":"2026-04-21","inLanguage":"en-GB","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://stackarchitect.xyz/#website"},"speakable":{"@type":"SpeakableSpecification","cssSelector":[".quick-answer p","h1"]}},{"@type":"BreadcrumbList","itemListElement":[{"@type":"ListItem","position":1,"name":"Home","item":"https://stackarchitect.xyz/"},{"@type":"ListItem","position":2,"name":"FAQ","item":"https://stackarchitect.xyz/faq"},{"@type":"ListItem","position":3,"name":"What Is Make.com?","item":"https://stackarchitect.xyz/faq/what-is-make-com"}]},{"@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"What is Make.com?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Make.com (formerly Integromat) is a no-code automation platform that connects apps and services using visual drag-and-drop workflows called scenarios. It uses triggers (events that start a workflow) and modules (actions that process or send data). For Shopify stores, Make.com is most commonly used for server-side conversion tracking, inventory management, TikTok CAPI, and P&L reporting — all running on the free tier of up to 1,000 operations per month."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is Make.com free?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. Make.com has a permanently free plan that includes 1,000 operations per month, unlimited scenarios, and access to all core integrations including Shopify, Google Sheets, Meta CAPI, Google Ads, and TikTok. For most Shopify stores processing under 300 orders per month, all four Stack Architect automations (CAPI Shield, Stocky Swap, TikTok CAPI, P&L Auto) run within the free tier indefinitely. Paid plans start at $9/month for 10,000 operations."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What is the difference between Make.com and Zapier?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Make.com and Zapier are both no-code automation platforms, but Make.com has significantly more generous free tier (1,000 operations vs Zapier's 100 tasks) and more powerful data transformation tools for complex workflows. Make.com uses a visual canvas with branching and looping logic; Zapier uses a linear step model. For Shopify server-side tracking and webhook-based automations, Make.com is the better choice due to its HTTP module, which allows direct API calls to Meta CAPI, Google Ads API, and TikTok Events API without needing pre-built integrations."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Does Make.com work with Shopify?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. Make.com has a native Shopify integration module and supports all Shopify webhook events including order created, order paid, customer created, and product updated. The most common Shopify use case is using an Order payment webhook to trigger automated workflows — this is the foundation of CAPI Shield, Stocky Swap, TikTok CAPI, and P&L Auto, all of which use a single Shopify webhook to trigger multiple simultaneous actions."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What is a Make.com scenario?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"A Make.com scenario is a visual automation workflow — a series of connected modules that run automatically when a trigger event occurs. A Shopify CAPI Shield scenario, for example, has a Shopify Order webhook as the trigger, followed by HTTP modules that POST purchase events to Meta CAPI and Google Enhanced Conversions. Scenarios can be exported and imported as JSON blueprint files — this is what the Stack Architect Complete Kit contains."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How many operations does Shopify automation use on Make.com?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Each module execution in a Make.com scenario counts as one operation. A typical Stack Architect setup running CAPI Shield, Stocky Swap, and P&L Auto simultaneously uses approximately 3–5 operations per Shopify order. On Make.com's free tier (1,000 operations/month), this supports approximately 200–333 orders per month before needing to upgrade to the $9/month Core plan (10,000 operations)."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What is the difference between Make.com and Shopify Flow?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Shopify Flow is built into Shopify and handles internal Shopify actions — tagging customers, adding order notes, sending Slack messages based on Shopify events. It cannot call external APIs directly. Make.com connects to external APIs — Meta CAPI, Google Ads API, TikTok Events API, Google Sheets — that Shopify Flow cannot reach. For server-side tracking and external data routing, Make.com is required."}}]}]})}/>
